1
00:00:00,487 --> 00:00:18,882
Namo Tassa Bhagavato Harahato Sama Sambuddhassa Namo Tassa Bhagavato Harahato Sama Sambuddhassa

2
00:00:19,640 --> 00:00:36,085
Namo tassa bhagavato harahato samma sambuddhassa Homage to the Buddha, the blessed, noble and fully self-enlightened one.

3
00:00:36,244 --> 00:00:41,091
Just a quick note about the technique.

4
00:00:42,954 --> 00:00:46,119
In the strict Mahasi tradition one doesn't stop noting.

5
00:00:48,427 --> 00:00:53,895
And the reason for that is that that which is noting is the discerning mind.

6
00:00:54,314 --> 00:00:56,658
For those of you who know your candas, that's the vijnana.

7
00:00:59,462 --> 00:01:05,209
It's the mind that is able to distinguish between black and white and know what something is for.

8
00:01:05,390 --> 00:01:08,894
It's that sort of, it's the higher faculty of the mind.

9
00:01:10,436 --> 00:01:15,162
And it works on basic perceptions, basic cognitions.

10
00:01:16,406 --> 00:01:24,397
And it uses words, it uses concepts, it uses images, but mainly it uses words, thinking.

11
00:01:27,540 --> 00:01:41,638
And at first, the beginner, when you start the Mahārājī, it's up front in your face, it's like you're watching yourself, all you're aware of are these words coming out of your head.

12
00:01:42,665 --> 00:01:53,316
And then as you keep displacing your attention on feeling, on sensation, the word, as it were, recedes or becomes like a quiet note in the background.

13
00:01:56,560 --> 00:02:11,997
As you then begin to settle in on an object, begin to fix in on an object, we were talking yesterday about this two stages of Vittaka-Vichara, the bee flying around the flower and the bee landing.

14
00:02:13,056 --> 00:02:40,853
so as you're noting the bees flying around the flower and then suddenly you find yourself as it were landing on the flower and the noting as it were again might seem to get in the way so the meditator stops the noting and before long they're wandering again because the landing on the flower has not matured okay

15
00:02:43,397 --> 00:03:02,318
If you say to yourself, well, my mind is really, my attention is steady, you know, like that's a thought that arises, I'm really steady on the rising and falling of some object, and you keep noting, that noting now, as it were, becomes as automatic.

16
00:03:03,513 --> 00:03:12,463
And sometimes you might find it more skillful not to note so much what it is you're experiencing, but the process of experiencing.

17
00:03:13,104 --> 00:03:23,877
So instead of saying something like pain, pain or something, or it might even be a subtle sensation for which there's no word, and you might use the word feeling.

18
00:03:24,899 --> 00:03:29,384
And you're using the word feeling to describe what it is you're actually feeling.

19
00:03:30,647 --> 00:03:37,000
But at that point, it's often more skillful to describe what you're actually doing, which is feeling the object.

20
00:03:37,801 --> 00:03:46,157
So when you say feeling, feeling, you're driving your attention closer and closer, more steady on the object in the act of feeling.

21
00:03:47,419 --> 00:03:49,443
You're actually feeling, right?

22
00:03:49,463 --> 00:03:52,689
Because this satipañña, this...

23
00:03:52,770 --> 00:04:06,109
awareness, intuitive intelligence, intuitive awareness has the ability not only to understand, observe at that level, but also directly feels, directly experiences.

24
00:04:08,612 --> 00:04:15,521
And at that point of when that bee really sort of sticks to the flower,

25
00:04:16,514 --> 00:04:29,891
You may be surprised to find that this very noting mind, as it were, distances itself, so that there's quite a clear separation between the knowing and the noting.

26
00:04:31,074 --> 00:04:36,261
And this noting carries on, because it's been conditioned to carry on discerning.

27
00:04:37,286 --> 00:04:45,242
So just like when you've learnt to walk, and now when you walk across the road, you don't have to be aware of your legs, the legs just do it.

28
00:04:46,303 --> 00:04:52,536
So this discerning mind keeps discerning, and you're aware of the object and this discerning mind.

29
00:04:52,615 --> 00:04:57,925
But the discerning mind is still helping you, is still keeping you on the object.

30
00:04:58,906 --> 00:05:00,831
See, still keeping you there.

31
00:05:01,552 --> 00:05:22,617
and in the classic Mahasi teaching you don't stop because at some point that bee as it were begins to so suck the nectar that it loses itself in the nectar and there's, it sounds a bit dramatic, a collapse

32
00:05:22,850 --> 00:05:49,887
there's a complete joining of this satipaññā with what it's actually experiencing at which point this thinking mind shuts down and at that point this satipaññā is at its purest not that insights can't come before that but at this point it is extremely pure and it's not something you can manufacture

33
00:05:50,120 --> 00:05:57,089
You can get yourself to that point by just diligently noting and diligently guiding your attention to the object.

34
00:05:57,670 --> 00:06:02,497
You can't make it collapse, because that collapse is a non-self experience.

35
00:06:03,540 --> 00:06:04,641
It's beyond your power.

36
00:06:05,583 --> 00:06:10,290
Because as soon as you say, let it collapse, there's somebody there saying, let it collapse.

37
00:06:10,769 --> 00:06:11,391
You can't do it.

38
00:06:12,452 --> 00:06:14,675
So that has to happen naturally.

39
00:06:14,790 --> 00:06:23,439
Now, it's very difficult, generally speaking, to arrive at that sort of concentration within a week.

40
00:06:23,579 --> 00:06:28,074
It takes, you know, because, well, we spent three days just getting it together.

41
00:06:28,915 --> 00:06:39,826
But if you do move towards the end of the week, towards that singularity, that feeling, it's like you almost feel it like a gear change, like there's a drop.

42
00:06:40,067 --> 00:06:41,528
People experience it in a different way.

43
00:06:42,309 --> 00:06:43,651
And you can feel yourself stuck.

44
00:06:44,310 --> 00:06:48,636
And the mistake is that the meditator thinks, oh, right now I'm really concentrating.

45
00:06:48,696 --> 00:06:49,617
So they stop the noting.

46
00:06:50,418 --> 00:06:53,420
The mind wanders and then it becomes a game, you see.

47
00:06:53,906 --> 00:07:04,355
So it's a case of being skillful at that point to not overestimate the level of concentration you've got, the level of focus you've got.

